-- Buffett boosts stake in Burlington Northern to 17.6 percent
-- 
-- Fri Jan 11, 2008 11:24am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/11/us-buffett-stake-idUSBNG31697220080111

 

 (Reuters) - Warren Buffett's Berkshire Hathaway Inc ( BRKa.N ) ( BRKb.N ) further increased its stake in Burlington Northern Santa Fe Corp BNI.N this week to about 17.6 percent. 

 According to a regulatory filing, Berkshire bought 751,400 shares in the U.S. railroad company for a total of about $58.1 million in the open market between January 7 and January 10. Buffett's company now owns 61.58 million shares. Burlington shares have fallen more than 16 percent till date after touching a year-high of $95.45 in April last year. They closed 2.8 percent higher at $80.06 Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange. Berkshire Hathaway has been gradually increasing its stake in Burlington Northern. The company reduced its stakes in two other railroads, Norfolk Southern Corp ( NSC.N ) and Union Pacific Corp ( UNP.N ), in October 2007. (Reporting by Dilipp S. Nag in Bangalore; Editing by  Kavita Chandran )